 they lived next door to a great tall water-chimney,
and one day as Elsie was washing at the sink, her little sister Lacie
jumped up beside her and peeped down into the chimney.

‘Where’s Nita?’ cried Lacie.  ‘Get down to us in a minute, Nita; we
can’t make out where she is.’

Nita was nowhere to be found, so they went andfetched her out of the
well.  Now, how was she to get down into the well again?

She said nothing of this to her mamma, but only told her that she had
lost her way on a piece of cake, and that she was very tired.  So they
let her go to bed.  But, my child, this is not all.  This is not the end of 




